{"award_age":63.0,"bio_image":"full\/6121ebfcd72b766c4c33fe3e721ad250cea52d91.jpg","category":"Peace","country":"Ghana","date_of_birth":"1938-04-08T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/7\/72\/Kofi_Annan_2012_%28cropped%29.jpg\/220px-Kofi_Annan_2012_%28cropped%29.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan","mini_bio":"<p><b>Kofi Atta Annan<\/b> (born 8 April 1938) is a <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Ghana\" title=\"Ghana\">Ghanaian<\/a> diplomat who served as the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Secretary-General_of_the_United_Nations#Secretaries-General\" title=\"Secretary-General of the United Nations\">seventh Secretary-General of the United Nations<\/a> from January 1997 to December 2006. Annan and the United Nations were the co-recipients of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/2001_Nobel_Peace_Prize\" title=\"2001 Nobel Peace Prize\">2001 Nobel Peace Prize<\/a> \"for their work for a better organized and more peaceful world.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_Peace_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan#cite_note-Nobel_Peace-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is the founder and the Chairman of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan_Foundation\" title=\"Kofi Annan Foundation\">Kofi Annan Foundation<\/a>, as well as being the chairman of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Elders_(organization)\" title=\"The Elders (organization)\">The Elders<\/a>, a group founded by <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nelson_Mandela\" title=\"Nelson Mandela\">Nelson Mandela<\/a>.<\/p><p>From 23 February until 31 August 2012, Annan was the UN\u2013<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Arab_League\" title=\"Arab League\">Arab League<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Special_Envoy_of_the_Secretary-General\" title=\"Special Envoy of the Secretary-General\">Joint Special Representative for<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Syria\" title=\"Syria\">Syria<\/a>, to help find a resolution to <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Syrian_civil_war\" title=\"Syrian civil war\" class=\"mw-redirect\">ongoing conflict<\/a> there.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan#cite_note-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Annan quit after becoming frustrated with the UN's lack of progress with regard to conflict resolution,<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> stating that \"when the Syrian people desperately need action, there continues to be finger-pointing and name-calling in the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_Nations_Security_Council\" title=\"United Nations Security Council\">Security Council<\/a>\". He has been involved in several humanitarian projects and won several awards including the Kora All Africa Music Lifetime Achievement Award in 2001.<sup id=\"cite_ref-koraawards.co.za_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Kofi_Annan#cite_note-koraawards.co.za-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Kofi Annan","place_of_birth":"Kumasi , Ghana","place_of_death":null,"text":"Kofi Annan , Peace, 2001","year":2001.0}